                                                                  BUSINESS QUESTION
                                             Which customer segments generate the highest revenue?

              Query
SELECT 
plan_type,
SUM(total_revenue) total_revenue,
COUNT(*)customer_count
FROM users
GROUP BY plan_type
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC;

                                         Findings: (what happened)
The business plan type had the highest number of revenue with fewer users (800) while the starter plan type had the lowest number of revenue with the highest users(2323)

                                             Why did it happen?
The Starter plan has the lowest monthly subscription price and also the largest customer base. Further analysis showed these customers have lower feature adoption, more support tickets, and lower satisfaction scores, which contributed to higher churn and lower revenue generation.
Why should leadership care?
Starter customers represent the company's largest customer segment, improving retention in this group could significantly reduce customer losses and protect recurring revenue.

                                               Recommendation?
Improve the onboarding experience for Starter customers, simplify access to key features, guiding users on how they will use the product effectively. Also, identifying customers submitting multiple support tickets and collecting early feedback to resolve product frustrations before they decide to leave.





                                                                                Q2. Business question
                                                                    Which industries generate the highest LTV?

                              
                                 Query
SELECT 
	industry,
	SUM(ltv_12m) lifetime_value,
	COUNT(*)users_count
FROM users
GROUP BY industry
ORDER BY lifetime_value DESC;

                                    


